Cook beef and onion in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 5 minutes or beef is browned and onion is tender; drain. Stir in seasoning mix and cook 2 more minutes. Stir in spinach, black beans and salsa and cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Spoon about 1/4 cup beef mixture evenly down center of each tortilla; sprinkle evenly with cheese. Roll up tortillas and top with sour cream, salsa, tomatoes and cilantro, if desired.